This app is awesome! The best app to analyze games that I've seen. You can 
import games for analysis and export games as well. You can be seeing what 
moves the strongest chess programs would do before each move you make. What 
I like best is that at any time in a game, if you see a move or line of 
play you think is good and don't understand why the program doesn't show it 
as the best or one of the good moves, you can actually start making them on 
the board seeing how the program replies to the move or line of moves you 
thought were good. Then you can go back into the move list and press on any 
move, then continue from there with the actual game by moving forward. It 
will then show you the new variation you tried, but will let you choose the 
new variation once again by pressing on that move highlighted differently 
in blue, or let you simply skip that new variation and continue with the 
actual game by simply pressing forward again when the new move variation is 
highlighted. No confusion, very user friendly. This is the analysis app I

replyContent: Thanks. The tips and tricks game is shown the first time you start the app. Tips and tricks are also mentioned on my Blog, You can use the Menu -- Help option to access that page.

content: Very useful!!!!
It would be desirable that this app has a alternative background, e.g. sepia. Thank you.

I hope you continue to develop this app with more features. One cool feature would be to add DGT Chessboard support via Bluetooth and USB. I don't believe there is any Android Chess app with DGT Chessboard support at this time. You are off to a good start.

I really like the app. It could be just me but I would like to be able to delete engines permanently to keep the list a bit more organized (instead of just unticking them).  Update: Thank you for the response :)! After some more use I would like to add some more ideas about updates of the UI. The tilting-to-move option sounds nice in theory but doesn't really work for me. Maybe swiping left and right on the board would be more intuitive option. Also an option to control the size of the buttons would be nice. My fingers are too big and sometimes it is hard to click the right one.
replyContent:
Noted! Thanks
Edit: BTW, you can always use the device's vol Up/Down key to move back and forth through the moves (instead of the on screen arrow keys)
